<section>
<h3>About Me</h3>

<p> 

I am a college student and programmer. My main area is distributed system, which I have been studying for 2 years and have done my <a href="/files/Monografia Mateus Antunes Braga.pdf">bachelor's thesis</a> in. The biggest project I have implemented is <a href="https://github.com/mateusbraga/freestore">FreeStore</a>, but I have a varied experience (see <a href="/files/Mateus%20Braga%20-%20Curriculo.pdf">Résumé</a>)

</p>

<p> 

Software for me is the challenge to solve a problem the simplest way possible. I believe that only this way we can control its complexity and understand its problems. No milaculous tools/practices matters if we don't understand what they do and what the project really needs. That is why I guide my projects through principles like: understand the problem, understand the solution, adopt simplifications and avoid generalizations.

</p>

<p> 

Regarding tecnologies, I prefer the Go programming language and a service-oriented architecture. I've had experience with Java, Python and Objective-C, but in my opinion they are not as productives to program in as Go. I use Linux for 5 years now and have developed a good understanding of how it works. Others tecnologies like Vi, Docker, Git, Amazon S3 and Google Appengine has its place in my projects.

</p>

<p>

I understand that tecnologies don't do miracles, and I reserved a significant time in my education to learn more about communication and leadership. My experience in CJR Junior Enterprise and in Toastmasters helped me a lot in this regard.

</p>

